# AMR-GigaWord 200k

# ::id 0 ::amr-annotator ISI-AMR-01 ::preferred
# ::tok new zealand share prices closed #.## percent higher thursday in the fourth straight day of gains , although there were signs the rally was losing momentum , dealers said .
# ::alignments
(c / close-01
      :ARG1 (p / price-01
            :ARG1 (s / share)
            :ARG1-of (n / new-01))
      :time (d / date-entity
            :weekday (t / thursday))
      :ARG1-of (h / have-degree-91
            :ARG2 (h2 / high-02
                  :ARG1 c)
            :ARG3 (m / more
                  :quant (p2 / percentage-entity
                        :value 4))
            :concession (s2 / signal-07
                  :ARG1 (l / lose-02
                        :ARG0 (r / rally-01)
                        :ARG1 (m2 / momentum))))
      :ARG1-of (s3 / say-01
            :ARG0 (p3 / person
                  :ARG0-of (d2 / deal-01))))

# ::id 1 ::amr-annotator ISI-AMR-01 ::preferred
# ::tok oil prices were higher in asian trading friday after overnight losses in new york as the market consolidated , dealers said .
# ::alignments
(s / say-01
      :ARG0 (p / person
            :ARG0-of (d / deal-01))
      :ARG1 (h / high-02
            :ARG1 (t / thing
                  :ARG2-of (p2 / price-01
                        :ARG1 (o / oil)))
            :time (d2 / date-entity
                  :weekday (f / friday))
            :time (a / after
                  :op1 (l / lose-02
                        :location (c / country
                              :name (n / name
                                    :op1 "New"
                                    :op2 "York"))
                        :time (o2 / overnight)
                        :time-of (c2 / consolidate-01
                              :ARG1 (m / market))))
            :ARG2-of (h2 / have-degree-91
                  :ARG1 t
                  :ARG3 (m2 / more))))

# ::id 2 ::amr-annotator ISI-AMR-01 ::preferred
# ::tok a un spokesman on thursday expressed concern over the continued feuds and skirmishes among different warlords in afghanistan , especially northern provinces .
# ::alignments
(e / express-01
      :ARG0 (p / person
            :ARG0-of (h / have-org-role-91
                  :polarity -
                  :ARG2 (s / spokesman)))
      :ARG1 (c / concern-01
            :ARG0 (c2 / continue-01
                  :ARG1 (a / and
                        :op1 (f / feud-01
                              :ARG0 (w / warlord
                                    :ARG1-of (d / differ-02)
                                    :location (c3 / country
                                          :name (n / name
                                                :op1 "Afghanistan")
                                          :part (n2 / north)
                                          :mod (e2 / especially))))
                        :op2 (c4 / clash-01
                              :ARG0 w)))
            :ARG1 p)
      :time (d2 / date-entity
            :weekday (t / thursday)))

# ::id 3 ::amr-annotator ISI-AMR-01 ::preferred
# ::tok a european health agency said sunday that ### new a\/h#n# flu cases were reported in european countries within the last ## hours .
# ::alignments
(s / say-01
      :ARG0 (a / agency
            :mod (h / health)
            :mod (c / continent
                  :name (n / name
                        :op1 "Europe")))
      :ARG1 (r / report-01
            :ARG1 (c2 / case-04
                  :ARG1 (d / disease
                        :name (n2 / name
                              :op1 "influenza"))
                  :ARG1-of (n3 / new-01))
            :location (c3 / country
                  :location c)
            :time (b / before
                  :op1 (n4 / now)
                  :duration (m / multiple
                        :op1 (t / temporal-quantity
                              :quant 1
                              :unit (h2 / hour)))))
      :time (d2 / date-entity
            :weekday (s2 / sunday)))

# ::id 4 ::amr-annotator ISI-AMR-01 ::preferred

                  :name (n2 / name

                        :op2 "Giles")

                        :ARG1 (c / county)
                        :ARG2 (c2 / colleague))
                  :ARG0-of (s2 / spinner-01)
                  :poss p)
            :ARG2 (ii / injure-01
                  :ARG1 (h2 / hip)
                  :ARG0-of (c3 / cast-01
                        :ARG1 (c4 / cloud)
                        :ARG2 (c5 / career
                              :poss (b / bowler
                                    :ARG1-of (s3 / slow-05)))))
            :ARG1-of (f / full-09)))

                        :ord (o / ordinal-entity
                              :value 4)))))

                  :mod (v / video)))
      :snt2 (p2 / prefer-01
            :ARG0 (h2 / he)
            :ARG1 (h3 / have-03
                  :ARG0 h2
                  :ARG1 (p3 / person
                        :ARG0-of (h4 / have-org-role-91
                              :ARG2 (o2 / official))
                        :quant (m2 / more))
                  :location (a / and
                        :op1 (f / field)
                        :op2 (a2 / around
                              :op1 f))
                  :ARG1-of (ii / instead-of-91))))

# ::id 7 ::amr-annotator ISI-AMR-01 ::preferred

                                          :ARG2-of (f / force-01)
                                          :location c2))
                              :mod (s / sanction-02
                                    :time (ii4 / immediate))))))
      :time (d2 / date-entity
            :weekday (w2 / wednesday)))

# ::id 8 ::amr-annotator ISI-AMR-01 ::preferred
# ::tok syria toughened its tone against israel on monday reversing weeks of growing optimism by accusing the jewish state of endangering their next round of peace negotiations .
# ::alignments
(t / toughen-01
      :ARG0 (c / country
            :name (n / name
                  :op1 "Syria"))
      :ARG1 (t2 / tone
            :poss c
            :prep-against (c2 / country
                  :name (n2 / name
                        :op1 "Israel")))
      :time (d / date-entity
            :weekday (m / monday))
      :manner (r / reverse-01
            :ARG0 c
            :ARG1 (w / week
                  :mod (o / optimism
                        :ARG1-of (g / grow-01)))
            :manner (a / accuse-01
                  :ARG0 c
                  :ARG1 c2
                  :ARG2 (e / endanger-01
                        :ARG0 (s / state
                              :mod (r2 / religious-group
                                    :name (n3 / name
                                          :op1 "Jew")))
                        :ARG1 (r3 / round
                              :mod (n4 / next)
                              :mod (n5 / negotiate-01
                                    :ARG0 c2
                                    :ARG2 (p / peace)))))))

      :ARG1 (g / grow-01

                        :name (n / name
                              :op1 "Peru")))

            :time (d / date-entity
                  :month 11)
            :time (a / after
                  :op1 (p / perform-02
                        :ARG0 e
                        :ARG1-of (f / fluctuate-01)
                        :duration (t / temporal-quantity
                              :quant 1
                              :unit (y / year)))))
      :ARG2 (w / worry-01
            :ARG0 (p2 / person
                  :ARG0-of (ii / invest-01))
            :ARG1 (p3 / possible-01
                  :ARG1 (h / hiccup
                        :mod (s / season)
                        :domain p
                        :ARG1-of (ii2 / instead-of-91
                              :ARG2 (s2 / signal-07
                                    :ARG0 p
                                    :ARG1 (p4 / pull-out-02
                                          :ARG1 e
                                          :ARG2 (r2 / recession-02
                                                :ARG1 e
                                                :ARG1-of (l / long-03
                                                      :ARG2 (t2 / temporal-quantity
                                                            :quant 1
                                                            :unit (y2 / year))))
                                          :time (f2 / final))))))))

# ::alignments
(s / say-01
      :ARG0 (p / person
            :ARG0-of (d / deal-01))
      :ARG1 (r / rise-01
            :ARG1 (p2 / price-01
                  :ARG1 (s2 / share
                        :mod (c / country
                              :name (n / name
                                    :op1 "Australia"))))
            :ARG2 (p3 / percentage-entity
                  :value "1/2")
            :time (d2 / date-entity
                  :weekday (t / thursday))
            :ARG1-of (c2 / cause-01
                  :ARG0 (r2 / ride-01
                        :ARG0 (p4 / person
                              :ARG0-of (ii / invest-01))
                        :ARG1 (t2 / tail
                              :part-of (r3 / rally-01
                                    :ARG1-of (s3 / strong-02)
                                    :location (m / market-sector
                                          :name (n2 / name
                                                :op1 "Wall"
                                                :op2 "Street")))
                              :mod (c3 / coat))))))
